skills: [u'Radiation Safety', u'Radiation Protection', u'Waste Management', u'Nuclear']
summary: Dr Chris Englefield CRadP FSRP FSyI.  I am a Chartered Radiation Protection Professional (CRadP), a Past-President and Fellow of the Society for Radiological Protection (FSRP), a Fellow of the Security Institute (FSyI), a member of the Institute of Nuclear Materials Management and a Member of the UK’s Emergency Planning Society (MEPS).  \n\nI previously worked for the Environment Agency (EA) as a senior regulator and manager.  The EA is (inter alia) the regulatory body in England for radioactive waste management, including the keeping and use of radioactive sources and their security. I am now an independent consultant (Isognos Limited).\n\nI have nearly 30 years of experience in radiation protection of which 23 have been spent in regulation.  I have represented the UK at the IAEA and EU level and have contributed to many IAEA  documents. I have trained regulators, customs officers, police and other government officers around the world in regulation and radiological counter-terrorism.  Recognised internationally as expert on radioactive source security, I chair the International Radiation Protection Association (IRPA) Working Group on Source Security.\n\nI am Editor-in-Chief of “Radiation Regulator” a free online open access journal that provides continuous professional development material to readers (predominantly but not exclusively regulators) in 73 countries around the world. Finally, I am an Honorary Fellow of the University of Cumbria supporting degree level courses in Radiation Protection and Nuclear Security Management.\n\nOutside of work I like to spend time with my wife and grown up children, and I also love sailing and wood-turning.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2011.9 ~ now', u'description': u'Odyssey is a 360-degree audio-visual interactive experience, incorporating motion controls with Kinect to allow for free motion. We have developed a solution which fully immerses the user\u2019s senses, offering an experience that is engaging and comparable to real life.\n\nWe have created an installation which combines a physical cylindrical screen made of plastic piping and stretchable fabric, and four short-throw projectors with image stitching software applied to create the display solution. We have also incorporated 5.1 surround sound speakers and Kinect-based motion controls to control movement. We have developed software in Unity and designed it to be experienced exclusively on the Odyssey platform.\n\nWe plan to further develop our software to take advantage of the innovative properties of the Odyssey platform, and refine the motion controls to deliver the most intuitive control scheme possible. We will also develop a permanent mounting system for our current installation, and will present a production-quality iteration of Odyssey at this year\u2019s ImagineRIT.', u'title': u'Odyssey'}]

summary: Graphic designer, writer and craft-maker - Maria Fung graduated with a BA (Hons) Graphic Design from the University for the Creative Arts in Maidstone, one of UK's leading creative universities, and has worked in London for a fun-filled 2 years.\n\nShe has worked at some of UK's top creative agencies like The Design Conspiracy and Stylorouge, where she collaborated with the team to design for musician David Gilmour, and at Deep where she designed for AEG Europe. Diversifying her design magic to other sectors such as entertainment, games, film, corporate, publishing, events, charity etc., Maria's clients include JEC, City College, the NHS, Sonic Music Festival, Run for Your lives - Asia, and ION Orchard. She briefly worked for BBDO in Singapore, one of the world's largest advertising agencies, working on projects for SingTel, NETS, Aviva, Drypers and BridgeAlliance.\n\nIn December 2006 and 2007, Maria was one of the 30 students selected to showcase their video works at the ODEON cinema, Maidstone, UK. Apart from having her works exhibited at the D&AD New Blood Show in London, 2007, Maria came in 2nd place at the internationally famous digital design tournament, Cut&Paste, London 2009. She has been featured in a variety of press such as Creative Sinergy, YCN, CulturePush and Web Design Index 9. Her articles can be seen in UK's leading creative recruitment website CreativePool, UCA Alumni Magazine, Vida De Latinos and Shiok.sg.\n\nMaria's 2-year stint at Zalora, South-East Asia's largest fashion e-store, has converted her into a lover of all things tech. When not at the computer, Maria loves to devote her time in DIY craft-making, gardening, travelling and participating in charitable activities.

summary: Call me a UI Developer, a Front-End developer, or just a developer. I work fast. I work smart. I work with little management. Tell me what business needs you have regarding web development and I'll do what I can go fill the need then report back for feedback. My code is clean, commented, properly indented, and overall easy to work with. My code is written with a modular and object oriented approach, even with CSS. I actually use the latest web standards, and to me it's not just a buzz word. Actually, I'm that annoying person who points out when there's a more standard and efficient way to code something. Yes, of course I make sure everything is responsive to work in screen sizes small and large, and on different devices and browsers. \n\nAs for the technical specifics, I try to stick closely to industry standards and guidelines. By default I hand code in HTML5/CSS3/JavaScript/jQuery/PHP and my solutions are fully responsive, from large monitors to small devices and a mobile-first approach. I prefer to use CSS pre-processors such as LESS or Sass to make stylesheet coding more efficient and easier to update/extend, but I am not dependent on them. Frameworks like Twitter Bootstrap, Foundation, and Bagpakk are no problem to use on projects, or I can create my own with documentation for the company to use, or none at all. Projects can have an agile process, but that is not required. Version control is preferably handled with Git.\n\nMy goal is to do good work that is useful and reusable all while bringing a friendly face to the team. You'll find that I can get along with pretty much anyone. I'm not interested in politics or drama, unless it's on TV or in books. I'm straightforward and will call things as I see them. I'm happy to brainstorm and have discussions on possibilities for the best directions for projects. Let's work together and get stuff done.

summary: Jenna Scifres Handmade Jewelry features unique, handmade jewelry in a minimalist style with a focus on comfort and quality.  Jenna Scifres grew up on a farm outside of Peoria, IL and loved collecting rocks and stones as a child and exploring the outdoors.  She started making jewelry as a hobby and the first piece of jewelry she created were tiny wire triangle earrings.\n\nWhat started as a hobby grew into a full time business in 2016.  Jenna loves making meaningful, personalized jewelry for her customers.  Jenna Scifres Handmade Jewelry specializes in name, initial, and birthstone jewelry as well as GPS coordinates jewelry, state or location jewelry, Morse code jewelry, roman numerals jewelry, and even pet ID tags.\n\nThe technique Jenna uses to create personalized jewelry is metal stamping.  A very different process than metal engraving with a machine, metal stamping means every letter and number is stamped individually one by one – completely done by hand.  Jenna Scifres Handmade Jewelry also uses high quality Swarovski birthstone crystals, semi-precious, and precious stones, often using raw and uncut gemstones.

summary: After a successful technical sales career in the aerospace/land turbine industry and traveling around the world, I decided to go into real estate full-time.  Originally I got my license in New Jersey in 1983 so my family could invest in residential real estate, then we moved multiple times up and down the east coast before coming to Arizona in 1995.  I decided that I wanted to work with family owned Realty Executives, a company of dedicated people, because of their company ethics and integrity.  It was a perfect match – I have been here over twelve years.\n\nI am a Realtor® working contracts to be a win-win for all involved, reducing the stress that comes with a detailed project.  I am an extremely hard worker whose enthusiasm is contagious.  I love to sell and people love to buy from me because I care.  I have a strong sense of ethics and I am a good communicator.  I work by referral, so send me your friends and family.  I hope to have the opportunity to work with you also!

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2012.8 ~ 2012.8', u'description': u'While taking the CECS 545 course at the University of Louisville, this is the very first project that the professor assigned and completed in one and a half week. Since, this project can be program in any programming languages, but I've decided to solve this problem in web forms.\n\nTraveling Salesperson Problem (TSP) was developed using ASP.net 4.0 framework in C#, HTML/CSS, JavaScript, and JQuery. The main purposes of this web application is to use Brute Force algorithm to to find the minimum cost solution to a Traveling Salesperson Problem.\n\nWhat is TSP? (See http://www.tsp.gatech.edu for more info)\n\nThe Brute Force algorithm is basically generating all possible tours and calculates the distances of each tour. Once figured out the distance of all possible tours and the shortest tour will be the best tour route.\n\nThere are four basic steps to solve the Travelling Salesperson Problem. Step 1 is to compute the total number of tours. Step 2 is to compute all the possible tours based on the number of cities. Step 3 is to compute the distance for each tour and finally step 4 is to get the best tour which is the shortest distance from all possible tours.\n\nCheck out the web app here:\nhttp://www.phibui.com/home/works/projects/TSP/Default.aspx', u'title': u'Traveling Salesperson Problem (TSP)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.8 ~ 2013.8', u'description': u'Implemented genetic algorithm to solve Quadratic Assignment Problem, and tried to improve it with Wisdom of Crowds approach. summary: I am a confident, independent self-starter with competitive drive, initiative, sense of urgency, and the ability to make decisions and take responsibility for them.  I can react and adjust quickly to changing conditions and come up with ideas for dealing with them.\n\nMy drive is purposeful, directed at getting things done quickly. I try to respond positively and actively to challenge and pressure, and have confidence in my ability to handle novel problems and people.  I am an outgoing, poised person, a lively and enthusiastic communicator, tending to be a little more authoritative than persuasive in style.  I tend at times to talk briskly, with assurance and conviction and am a stimulating influence on others, while being firm, direct, and self-assured in dealing with them.\n\nMy work pace is distinctly faster-than-average.  I learn and take action quickly.  On the other hand, I can become impatient and restless working repetitively with routine details or structured work, and tend to delegate such work if my position permits, and will follow up, focusing on completion and accomplishment, rather than how things were done.  With an interest in other people and their development, I will delegate authority, limiting such delegation to people in whom I have high levels of confidence, and following up with pressure for timely results.\n\nI’m confident in my assumptions about any missing information, and am comfortable acting even in the absence of complete information. For me, continual progress towards the general goal is more important than always being exactly on track; I’m flexible and will make course corrections as necessary, when the time arises.\n\nSure of myself, I set high standards of achievement for me and others and look for opportunities to compete and to win.  Venturesome, I’m stimulated by new challenges and situations, generally driving myself and others to new horizons. I’m ambitious both for myself and for the team(s) which I participate on.

summary: I vividly recall the first computer I ever owned. It was a VTech PreComputer 2000 with a 2 line LCD screen that my parents bought me when I was 8 or 9. The first thing I did when I got it was open up the instruction manual and start teaching myself BASIC. \n\nTo this day, I approach every project, business, and relationship with that same focused, thoughtful fervor. I'm always exploring new opportunities and testing my limits, learning as I go and expanding my knowledge and skills to keep pace with the rapid rate at which my ambitions rise.\n\nI've worn many hats throughout the years.\n\nI worked as a Social Media Strategist for Zaarly when they were just cutting their teeth. I helped expand their operations into Los Angeles and San Francisco by targeting key influencers and engaging with them via Twitter and Facebook.\n\nI jumped in to IT as a Store Technician for Sunshine Energy. While there, I cobbled together a program for remotely administrating and updating their store computers by augmenting their POS system (PDI), saving the company time and money by reducing the need for them to send a tech out to the store. I eventually earned a position as Assistant IT Director.\n\nI flexed my programming prowess as an Interactive Web Developer for VML. I worked alongside some of their best and brightest developing a Facebook application for Gatorade. While there, I also carried the torch as organizer and speaker for Afternoon Tea, a developer's group aimed at raising the bar for front-end standards at VML.\n\nLastly, I've been blessed with the opportunity to act as Director of Infrastructure & Operations for CandyCam and work alongside some of the most talented and charismatic people I've ever met.\n\nIf you're interested in me, what I do, or simply want to connect, please, contact me! I'm highly engaged in the tech and entrepreneurial communities in Kansas City and am always looking to expand my network. I also really enjoy helping people, so if you need something, let me know!

summary: With experiences in managing programs and projects worth over 10 billion USD in the sectors of Oil & Gas, Business, IT, Construction, Finance and Banking, Politics, Government, Healthcare, Automotive, FMCGs and Economic Development, Emad has accumulated a rich pool of knowledge and expertise that he puts to work to transform organizations by translating their strategic objectives into tangible results and realizing anticipated benefits. Emad specializes in strategy execution, organizational change management, the management of complex multidisciplinary programs and projects, rescuing troubled projects, as well as the setup, alignment and operation of Portfolio, Program, and Project Management Offices (PMOs). \n\nMember of the core team developing the Third Edition of the Project Manager Competency Development Framework (PMCDF) PMI Standard,\nSubject Matter Expert on the following PMI Standards:\n- Standard for Organizational Project Management (OPM), \n- Standard for Program Management Fourth Edition\n- Standard for Portfolio Management, Fourth Edition\nLast Manager of the PMI® IT and Telecommunications Community of Practice, \nFounder and First Chair of the PMI® Egypt Chapter, \nPast board member of the Agency for the Development and Empowerment of Women (ADEW),\nPast Evaluator of submissions for PMI® Professional Awards for Individual Recognition, \nSteering Committee member & Chair of the Consultancy, Training, & Development Committee of the Egyptian Junior Business Association (EJB),\nPast member of the Advisory Panel to the White House Business Council, \nMember of the Industry Advisory Council to the American Public University System (APUS)\nPublished Author and featured in various publications such as PM Network (PMI®), \nSpeaker at PMI® Global Congresses in North America and EMEA since 2012.\nFounder of the ‘Projects to the Point (P2P) Conference and Exhibition’ www.p2pevents.net\nIn 2008, facilitated the first ever agreement between PMI® and a government (Egypt).

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2015.10 ~ 2015.10', u'description': u'GoIT suggested students to participate in some kind of battle to see our professional growing. The battle is called Frontend Challenge. This competition became the acid test of our skills and let us experience the realities of the IT world.\n\nThe battle is conceived for the teams, which are created by a toss. Every team should be composed of students with different levels of skills.\n\nBecause of the Frontend Challenge we`ve raised the level of our team work and have found the way to distribute the roles in the project in more rational and correct way. The result of a two-week work you can see as a ready to service portfolio site of our team. Which purpose is presentation of the development team. Style, design, concept, methods of implementation and realization have been defined and selected by ourselves.\n\nThe site should have contain a list of mandatory requirements and elements:\n\u2022 HTML is uniform for all types of layouts. projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2013.12 ~ 2014.4', u'description': u'CA Technologies required an application to provide employees a way of creating, updating or removing Knowledge Based Articles for clients requesting information. Utilizing the SharePoint 2013 App model (CSOM) and latest Web Frameworks including Bootstrap, KnockoutJS, Typescript, JQuery and REST API an App was created and made deployable to multiple servers. This app had to provide data from legacy systems to create forms for tagging and associating products to the authoring article. To support older browsers and keep a consistent look a WYSIWYG Editor was selected in place of the default SharePoint rich text editor. Data from legacy Systems would be imported through services, and placed into the Managed Metadata Services to provide a highly cached location for quick lookups as well as a possible way to navigate the site. Cross Site publishing would be used to allow for Searches from other site collections and to keep a separation from authoring. SharePoint Workflows were put in place to move the Articles between stages such as Editing, Pending, Approved and Rejected. Once Approved the Article would be published providing support for clients and a way to read Solutions, FAQ\u2019s or other information from Subject Matter Experts.', u'title': u'Support Self Service (ECM)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.11 ~ 2013.11', u'description': u'.NET security application automating reverse penetration of large networks. Additional information confidential.', u'title': u'TEDI Alamo'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.7 ~ 2015.7', u'description': u'', u'title': u'MediaCom - McStream'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.10 ~ 2014.10', u'description': u'The primary business goal of www.css-i.com  was to provide potential and current clients with a means of access to request, learn and connect with Corporate Software Solutions inc. (CSSi) about current, past and future services.  \n\nThe Decision to use SharePoint Online was made to provide all users a uniform experience with centralized access to data.   Branded with BootStrap the responsive masterpage caches 90% of the css and javascripts used throughout the site, creating a faster page load for both mobile as well as desktop users. The use of AngularJS, KnockoutJS and JQuery was made as client side rendering would allow for a lighter footprint, easily updated data and layouts as templates and content could be stored in lists throughout the site, and a snappier experience as the browser would handle user interactions and request data as it is needed. \nThrough Sharepoint Online Team Sites, Development sites, and App sites.  The teams at CSSi would be able to access apps, past projects, current projects, and current documentation based on their user account, while workflows and client access would allow customers to view updates on current projects as well as make requests to change provided documentation and services.  Unauthorized users are limited as they would only have access to view the public site, and create requests for client access or services through the new Contact us form.  \n\nAs more apps and services are provided by CSSi this website will be updated to accommodate relevant announcements, Blog and Learn tutorials on SharePoint as well as other Microsoft Services and provide new and improved means to create requests to become a part of our Solution to the ever changing development of Software.\n', u'title': u'CSSi SharePoint Online'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.6 ~ 2013.6', u'description': u'Using Silverlight, WCF RIA and MS SQL Server. This application created translatable items by merging style information from the Legacy ERP and PLM systems.  These items were then placed in an updateable grid for outside vendors to translate style as well as material information from English into Chines.  After validation an item export to Excel allowed vendors to import data into applications which were used for printing hangtags. ', u'title': u'China Collaboration Utility'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.1 ~ 2016.1', u'description': u'Financial Analysts(FA) at leading firms have requested new forms of software, which will help keep potential clients both engaged in the meeting as well as informed of how their assets will handle throughout their life.  The leading charts and graphs applications are boring, and are little help to a FA in selling additional services.\nThe new application needed to be fast, mobile friendly, future proofed, and fun to work with.  To get the process going we utilized these frameworks and services with explanations below.  The Main development framework was Angular 2(using the cli and Typescript), GreenSock Animation, WebWorkers(special gulp process to facilitate this and keep compliance with Angular-CLI) Azure Active Directory(AAD) for Enterprise Integration, and ASP.net with Entity Framework Core.  The Angular CLI was used to keep the project within best patterns and practices with the teams at google and the communities.  A new Development pattern was created to use the Web Worker process, which allows the UX to be both responsive while also cutting down processing time as the data processes are done on a separate thread within the browser.  The Animations were performed by supplying data to GreenSock Framework, and authentication for the General public was ASP.Net Identity Framework.  Later discussions on AAD integration for Enterprises were discussed, but not yet implemented.  Using AAD would allow access to other applications which can provide data for faster integration as well as Single Sign On Experience from their Work computers.\n', u'title': u'Cinematic Financial Software'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2013.1 ~ 2013.1', u'description': u'Utilizing Silverlight, WCF and MS SQL Server. This application created items, which will be tracked as they moved from location to location. Based on sales orders pulled from the ERP the teams are able to use sales logic in making decisions on whether to send samples to locations or not.  The location audit logging would ensure that an item already sent to a location would not be sent more than one time unless requested by client.  Tabs for Search and Barcode Scanning allowed users to create a list for quick check-in or checkout to locations. Dynamic barcode generation and label creation of single items allowed end users to create items, barcodes, and labels as they were acquired or an Excel template would be used for Mass item creation.', u'title': u'Sample Tracking Accessories'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2015.6 ~ 2016.7', u'description': u'Despite the wealth of information and metrics gathered in the current system, regular users are provided with no tangible benefits or insights from adding their local market information. Reports are generated off the old system (rather than being an integral part of it) and these are used at global and executive level and for reporting figures upwards. This requirement still remains however one of the drivers of the new solution is to provide analytics at a local market level, information that will, with the insights presented, drive their new business activity, focus their attention on potential new clients and sectors and provide a further incentive to use the system and keep their information up to date and relevant.\n\nThe Use of AngularJS and a new development strategy applied (based off the App Model) was decided as the key framework and architectural components to the application.  the development strategy allowed for advanced security, removal from the company app catalog, modular deployments(Continuous Integration is possible if required, but Administrating company handled deployments manually) on different tiers as well as fast migration to Azure services and SharePoint Online in future migrations.  PowerBi was used as a main reporting feature providing reports for users whom wanted to use IPad's as well as those looking for customizable reports without further development.  There were a some custom reports built by consulting Development firm as well.\n\nfor more information about Development process and technologies please message me.', u'title': u'MediaCom - McDab V2 SharePoint 2013 AngularJS App'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.6 ~ 2012.6', u'description': u'Utilizing Silverlight, WCF and MS SQL Server. This application provides outside vendors as well as internal users access to current style information and used HS numbers. Color coded text was used for quick reference to correct and incorrect codes, which were validated against ERP application, while background coloring at the Item level provided information on last updated based on PLM last update vs. the users last updated to specific item. Once interaction with the item was validated the result checked new numbers and rates against ERP, and removed coloring to the background. A comments section allows for quick collaboration on items with time stamps and users were logged to ensure questions were correctly answered by the proper administrators. The images on each item would provide vendors with validation necessary for specifics on duty rates, while caching and key value pair calls to the services would decrease network traffic. There was an excel export given to users for easy to read access of the work already done, and information on items at a given period of time. System updates through SSIS pulled style data from PLM system, while HS Numbers were pulled from the ERP for validation before uploading.', u'title': u'HS Codes( Harmonized System Codes)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2017.2 ~ now', u'description': u'Since SharePoint Online will soon remove the public feature, a New cleaner version of www.css-i.com needed to be created.  \nusing pure Bootstrap and ASP.NET razor, the new main site was designed to be SEO friendly and provide a clean Single Page User Experience.  Services to decrease load times are supported by an Azure infrastructure from Blob Storage for Images, CSS and JS files,  Azure CDN Servers (GEO Replication and Caching enabled) helps decrease Network load time, while Azure SQL and App services for the rest of the website.   This Core Foundation in Azure will also support the Blog and Resume subsites.  more information on these as they are finished.', u'title': u'CSSi Website V2'}]

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2014.8 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'Apex Systems Inc. is an IT staffing and workforce solutions firm that specializes in providing IT professionals for contract, contract-to-hire and direct placements. They were using a SAP system for their primary report delivery and this system was being phased out, so they needed to be able to reproduce all existing reports that were no longer going to be supported by SAP. The recommended solution was to build a SSAS Tabular model based on the existing SAP data model. I worked with Jason Coats of TCSC and Scott Sager of APEX to design, build, secure, and deploy the SSAS data model architecture. The report delivery method was Excel PowerPivot, so reports could be highly scalable and leveraged by a broad range of users.', u'title': u'APEX Systems - SSAS Tabular Model'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.8 ~ 2016.8', u'description': u'Built an iterative forecasting system in R that runs multiple forecasts models against every course offered at Liberty University in order to find the best forecast model possible for future course enrollment. The best/most accurate model is then automatically selected and displayed in a Tableau dashboard along with the other forecast model results, so the user can have the best idea of all forecast results.', u'title': u'Liberty University - Course Enrollment Forecasting'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.10 ~ 2014.12', u'description': u'University of Virginia Facilities was looking for a way to produce better estimates and more accurate predictions for the utility consumption for all campus buildings and all units of measure on an hourly basis. University of Virginia Facilities had about 12 different power consumption measures. The forecast extended 48 hours into the future, because the model was heavily driven on weather forecasts which were provided by the forecast.io weather service. The forecast.io API was used to obtain hourly weather forecast data through R. The forecast model results were delivered to a CSV under a shared file location, and a SSIS package was built to insert that data into their primary database, so they could display the forecasts on a dashboard module.', u'title': u'UVA Facilities - Utilities Forecasting Model'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.1 ~ 2014.8', u'description': u'Cannon Design is an international architecture and design firm that specializes in facility planning and assessment. Their primary internal web and mobile applications were in need of stabilization and enhancement to better serve their mobile workforce of property assessors. I worked closely with Cannon\u2019s technical team as lead consultant and developer to re-architect and refresh the facility management application. The project included a mixture of .Net, HTML5, and client side technologies. The existing client side implementation was improved by consolidating and abstracting Web SQL functionality into a JavaScript data layer. The website was converted from a web site to a web application that utilized managed builds, publishing and code analysis. A suite of SSRS reports was created and integrated into the web application to provide better insight into their deliverables.\n', u'title': u'Cannon Design - Facility Optimization'}]

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2010.1 ~ 2010.1', u'description': u'Induced Draft fans at Kothagudem Thermal Power Station (KTPS) located in Andhra Pradesh, India were analysed under various operating conditions. Project also included inspection, collection and analysis of power generation data to address load dispatch issues. ', u'title': u'Analysis of Induced Draft Fans in Thermal Power Plant & Load Dispatch Issues.'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.8 ~ 2012.12', u'description': u'With the increase in penetration of Solar PV, there are many issues related to integration of solar into our distribution grid. It is very crucial to analyse the response of grid when power flows from load centers to generating stations. That's when SMART grid comes into picture. \n\nSolar Forecasting has the capability to increase the reliability of Solar Systems. It projects Solar PV as the technology of the future.', u'title': u'Solar Integration and Solar Forecasting'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2009.8 ~ 2009.12', u'description': u'The project included analysis of Switchgear used in transmission and distribution system in Hyderabad, India. Zones of Protection and necessary switchgear required were identified.', u'title': u'Application of Switchgear in a Transmission and Distribution System'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2010.2 ~ 2010.4', u'description': u'The rotor was selected to have 36 slots with 2 layer winding. All the 72 terminals were brought out of the motor and connections were changed in such a way that it caused change in number of poles. Hence a motor with single winding was redesigned to run on multiple speeds.', u'title': u'Designed a Three Phase Induction Motor on Pole Amplitude Modulation'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.11 ~ 2011.11', u'description': u'The tools used in this project are MATLAB and Simulink Model. The CUBE controllability and Observability have been verified and implemented the state feedback controller u= -kx using Simulink model. With the desired Eigen values we designed and implemented the estimator in MATLAB. In the waveform of scope for the estimator, we observe that the output of two states first overshoot and then go to zero. Also, in the waveform of scope for the controller, we observe that the five states first overshoot and then go to zero. These five states are then multiplied by the controller gain K and give a scalar output. So, our controller is able to stabilize the system.', u'title': u'Stabilization of a cube system using MATLAB and Simulink'}]

summary: I am a TS/SCI cleared Database Administrator in the Washington D.C. area with nearly 8 years of professional experience.\n\nI had my first WAMP (Windows-Apache-MySQL-PHP) stack in high school on a low-powered server in my bedroom. In college, it was upgraded to LAMP (Linux-Apache-MySQL-PHP). When I learned the elegance of relational algebra and the power of SQL, I started to focus on relational databases.\n\nI prefer to stay consistently challenged in my professional career. If my work becomes too routine, I get bored easily. My current interests are:\n\nDatabase Security\n&#149; Row-level security solutions in FOSS databases, such as MySQL and PostgreSQL.\n&#149; Linking FOSS database security controls to external authorization sources.\n&#149; Making data security nearly invisible to the application.\n\nHigh Availability\n&#149; The various use cases for standard MySQL replication, Galera Cluster, and MariaDB's multi-source replication.\n&#149; Streamlining PostgreSQL streaming replication with RepMgr.\n&#149; Automating failover with Pacemaker and Corosync.

summary: Clearance: Active Secret\n\nAdaptable Business Analyst with specialty in Requirements Gathering, Requirements documentation and Quality Assurance. Solid understanding of all phases of the System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) to include Agile and Waterfall methodologies. Highly effective at interpreting business requests into requirements, ensuring that they are delivered as expected, and providing strategic direction for senior management. \n\nFormally trained as a Project Manager, Business Analyst, and Quality Assurance Analyst with strong skills in analysis, problem solving, requirements elicitation and communication. Skilled at converting complex business and end-users needs into easy to understand technological terms and functional requirements to meet business objectives.    \n\nPreviously led software test analyst while assigned to the Air Force Combat Weather Center, Hurlburt Field, FL.  Hand selected as lead software test analyst for a $200M Air Force weather system upgrade, where I oversaw the development of testing requirements, reviewed system requirements, convened on 10 working groups, and was one of the final members on the source selection team for the Joint Environmental Toolkit program. \n\nI have experience in managing software testing project, developing test cases, analyzing data, and possess the ability to complete projects ahead of schedule and within budget constraints.  \n\nI have been repeatedly recognized for developing innovative and excellent results when given difficult tasks.  Critical thinking and the never ending pursuit of determining if it can be improved, enhanced, easier and cheaper have set me apart from my peers.

summary: As founder and CEO of QA InfoTech Worldwide, Mukesh is responsible for the company's vision and leads the organization's worldwide operations, marketing, sales and development efforts. He founded QA InfoTech with a vision to provide unbiased Quality Assurance (QA) testing solutions and has grown the organization to four Centers of Excellence globally. \nMukesh began his technology career with DCM Data Systems and then worked at IBM Corporation, Quark Inc., Gale Group and Adobe Systems in software engineering and testing roles. He has a passion for excellence, an eye for detail and commitment towards customers, and blends it with an execution style that has the maturity of an established organization with the nimbleness of a startup – these together have enabled QA InfoTech stand apart in the exceedingly competitive software testing industry. Under his guidance, the company has contributed to various innovative quality assurance and test-automation solutions. He continues to actively evangelize software testing as a career and its indispensable aspects in today’s world of software engineering. He has authored three books in these areas to benefit testers and engineers at all levels – these include “Are You Smart Enough To Be A Tester”, “Leverage The Wisdom of the Crowd in Software Testing” and “Software Testing 2020: Preparing for New Roles”\n\nMukesh is an avid reader, golfer and cricket player, as well as a philanthropist who takes a personal interest in the organization’s CSR initiatives.\n

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2017.1 ~ 2017.2', u'description': u'At TATA Steel a Quintiq system (APS) is implemented for the inbound supply chain.  Nathalie helped the team set up a testingpolicy and -proces and helped determine - together with the APS team- which tests could be selected and how to design them so that the goal \', u'title': u'Tata Steel Europe - Inbound Supply Chain'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.5 ~ 2012.12', u'description': u'HIP, mortgages in progress is the project at ING that implemented the new mid office system (Force) for mortgages and merged the two back offices (Hy and HyPOS) of old Postbank and ING (migration). As test manager I was responsible for all testing activities of the mortgages migration and was asked to \u2013complementary to the assignment- act as test coordinator for the implementation of the mid office package. \nING was able to implement the mortgage mid office package and migrate the mortgage portfolio successfully. I explicitly received the compliment that my calmness during this high risk and stressful project was appreciated. Nice fact: the migration of circa 27 billion was finalized with only 2 eurocents difference!', u'title': u'HIP (mortgage portfolio migration) at ING'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2005.9 ~ 2005.11', u'description': u'Postbank had a scoop in 2015 in the Netherlands; designing a payment card with a standard of personal image, the so-called \u2018MijnPostbankPas\u2019. I planned, designed and executed the End2End-tests for this project; from requesting the card in the \u2018fitting room\u2019 to the actual hand-out of the card at the post office and a pilot that had 12000 instead of 6000 participants and can probably be marked as one of the first \u2018virals\u2019 in the Netherlands!\nPostbank was able to introduce the MijnPostbankPas successfully without the risks that might have occurred without testing.', u'title': u'Mijn PostbankPas (project \'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2016.3 ~ 2016.12', u'description': u'My assignment at the Police started with conducting an investigation to the current status of test automation within five appointed projects and to give an advice based on the outcomes of this investigation to implement or optimize test automation so it supports Agile or DevOps development. \nThe deliverables I made were a report with the results and recommendations that can be used as reference guide and a practical one pager which the organization can use to start with the actions recommended. The deliverables were presented and the choices and actions are actively marketed into the organization in my role as coach testautomation. The topics coached upon were categorized under 'career' (how to cultivale skill), 'knowledge' (how to optimize sharing and secure knowledge), 'practical' (alignment in approaches, agreements and the actual automation itself) and 'beneficial' (TDD and TDM). At the end of the assignment I again conducted an investigation to the status to verify the progress made, resulting in a follow-up report and to-do list for my (internal) successor.', u'title': u'Coach TestAutomation - Politie'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2007.6 ~ 2011.5', u'description': u'The NS Hispeed Ticketing program is responsible for the development and adjustments of software, systems and processes with regards to ticketing within NS Hispeed. \nThis consist of tickets for the new high speed train \u2019FYRA\u2019 but also new ticketing concepts like OV Chip card and Home print. The NS Hispeed organization also didn\u2019t have a test organization and \u2013process when I started at this assignment. I started as test coordinator for domestic products where I performed acceptance testing, End2End testing, integration testing and production testing (Try Out). I was regularly asked for advise on other projects and processes and I was able to set-up a testing process and test desk. Because \u2018domestic products\u2019 was finalized with excellent results the commitment was extended for \u2018international products\u2019. \nCurrently the successful implementation is still viewable by the special poles on the HSL-stations and the choose able HSL product on the yellow vending machines.', u'title': u'Albatros (FYRA) - NS Hispeed'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2017.3 ~ now', u'description': u'Nathalie has set-up the test strategy for BI-testing in an agile environment at ETOS BI. ', u'title': u'Jeugdzorg WIJZ'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2005.11 ~ 2007.5', u'description': u'Rabobank International Risk uses different applications and systems to perform risk calculations. summary: I am a senior test consultant and regional service lead at Assurity Consulting Ltd.  I am an advocate for structured exploratory testing techniques such as session-based and thread-based test management. \n\nAs well as delivering onsite testing services for clients, I am active in coaching, and delivering training, having co-created and continue to deliver Assurity's Testing Overdrive software testing course (http://assurity.co.nz/education/courses/55)\n\nI am active in the software testing community; I co-founded WeTest work shops in Wellington with Katrina Clokie, and regularly blog and tweet about software testing (http://testerkiwi.blogspot.com/ & @AWGHodder). \n\nI have spoken at STANZ, CAST, and Let's Test conferences about using leaner approaches to test planning and reporting and using visual tools such as mindmapping software as a learning, testing planning, and communication tool. I have attended the invite-only Kiwi Workshop on Software Testing peer conference every year it has been running.\n\nAs well as a keen interest in general software testing, I also have a particular interest in UX areas such as user research and usability testing.

projects: [{u'timePeriod': u'2002.1 ~ now', u'description': u'Software testing is a critical component of the software development process and is required to ensure the safety, robustness and usability of software. Unfortunately, it is also complex, labor intensive and expensive, accounting for almost 67% of the total cost of software development. Hence, there has been significant research aimed at automating the testing process. Although automation has achieved some success, many problems remain.  In particular, it is not yet clear how to automate the testing of graphical user interfaces (GUIs), which constitute an increasingly large portion of software systems (almost 50% of the total software code). Recognizing the importance of GUI testing, we have developed GUITAR, a GUI Testing Framework that presents a unified solution to the GUI testing problem. In the last 15 years, we have had considerable success in developing new technologies for GUI testing.', u'title': u'GUI Testing Framework'}]

summary: SKILL HIGHLIGHTS\no Raised and managed more than $4 Million for 12 projects on cyber security, mobile malware,\ncontinuous building/testing, user experience evaluation, and machine learning.\no Ranked 8th among Top scholars in the field of systems and software engineering, (2003–2007).\no Founded and currently heading the Event Driven Software Lab at the University of Maryland.\no Identified new research projects based on the needs of industry and market conditions, formed and headed research teams across diverse fields and multiple continents, and developed open-source products as tangible outcomes.\no Pioneered the field of model-based Graphical-User Interface (GUI) testing, and championed its adoption into mainstream research and practice.\no Invented GUITAR (a GUI testing framework), GUI Ripping (a GUI reverse engineering technology), and Event-Flow Graphs (a workflow model of the software), now used by researchers worldwide.\no Founded TESTing Techniques & Experimentation Benchmarks for Event-Driven Software, and Experimental Evaluation of Software and Systems in Computer Science, both now successful annual workshops.\no Evaluated large data using sampling approaches, experiments, causal modeling, and data mining techniques to make statistical arguments, develop visualizations, perform longitudinal analysis, survey nonresponse analysis, entropy measurement, and validity/reliability analysis.\no Managed all aspects of project accounting and budgeting, focusing both on the highest-priority short- term needs as well as planning for the next big challenge.\no Delivered projects in a fast paced, ever changing and ambiguous environment.\no Formed teams from the ground up by directly hiring programmers, researchers, and students.\no Heading the International Conference on Software Testing in Tokyo in 2017.\no Authored over 130 peer-reviewed papers and edited 8 book volumes.\no Gave invited talks at more than 50 venues. \no Details in CV at http://www.cs.umd.edu/~atif/cv.pdf

summary: I am a multi-faceted and versatile software engineer, who has undertaken responsibilities in various aspects of software development, whether it is requirements analysis, design, development or debugging support issues. I have been extensively involved in scalable enterprise web applications for the last decade and continually invest time in mastering the Java EE platform. My open source contributions to JBoss Arquillian, ShrinkWrap, and many other projects would serve as a testament to that effect. Being the web platform an important part of my daily job, I am a strong advocate of the web for everyone and work as an invited expert for two W3C working groups.\n\nThe primary skill in accomplishing my tasks has been research. This is evidenced in my ability to understand the relevant industry standards and specifications, and to apply the knowledge gleaned to the problem at hand.\n\nIn the accomplishment of my responsibilities, I have demonstrated the ability to understand the behavior of systems at the lowest desirable level, lending me insight in to the root causes of issues in various aspects - transaction management, concurrency, deployment, internationalization, clustering, scalability and performance. This enabled me to pinpoint erroneous behavior and correct them in a timely manner.\n\nSpecialties:\n• Java / Java EE: Servlets & JSPs, EJBs, CDI, Bean Validation, Web Services (JAX-WS and JAX-RS), JMS, Cache API and Data Grids, JPA (Hibernate)\n• Application servers: WildFly, JBoss AS, GlassFish, Tomcat\n• Java MVC frameworks: Stripes Framework, Struts\n• Web: HTML, CSS, JavaScript\n• JavaScript frameworks: AngularJS, jQuery\n• Testing frameworks: JUnit, TestNG, Arquillian, Jasmine, Karma\n• Build tools: Maven, Ant, Yeoman, Gulp, Grunt\n• Version control systems: Git, Subversion, CVS\n• Reporting Tools: BIRT, JasperReports

summary: Ashwin Karpe currently serves as the Enterprise Integration Practice Lead for North America at Red Hat. Ashwin leads a team of Practice Architects and Subject Matter Experts in the development, delivery, and enablement of enterprise level repeatable solutions within the Red Hat Consulting Emerging Technology Practice.\n\nHe has over two decades of experience and a proven track record in designing, developing and modeling large distributed enterprise systems with several successfully executed middleware projects around SOA and Distributed Computing technologies.\n \nAshwin is an elected Apache Camel Committer and PMC Member at the Apache Software Foundation and has contributed several components to the Apache Camel, ServiceMix, ActiveMQ and CXF community projects. He is also a current member of the Red Hat JBoss SOA Platform 6 (JBoss Switchyard) Engineering team and implements complex solutions around the new and emerging product portfolio. \n\nAshwin is well versed in open source technologies. In addition to delivering complex software integration and infrastructure projects, he has developed/conducted seminars, webinars and training courses on all Red Hat JBoss FUSE offerings (based on well-known Apache projects). \n\nHe has deep knowledge of the Finance and Telecommunications verticals and represented IONA in several Telecom standards initiatives at the Tele-Management Forum (TMF) and Parlay for standards such as TMF 814 and MTOSI. \n\nSpecialties: Apache projects: Camel, CXF, Servicemix, Karaf, ActiveMQ, Lucene, XML Security, Shiro, ZooKeeper among others\n                   JBoss projects: SOA-P 6 (Switchyard), Netty\n                   Telecom Element and Network Management Systems\n                   SOA and Distributed Computing

Cummulative Patch (CP) Stream'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2011.3 ~ 2011.6', u'description': u'Creating modular architecture for EAP/EWP Continuous integration using Jenkins CI. summary: Tim Mitchell is a data architect, author, speaker, and trainer.  He has been delivering data solutions for more than 14 years, focused primarily in data warehousing, ETL/SSIS, database development, and reporting.  He has earned a number of industry certifications and holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science from Texas A&M at Commerce, and has been a Microsoft Data Platform MVP since 2010. Tim is the founder and principal data architect of Tyleris Data Solutions, a consulting firm focused on delivering data solutions with an unparalleled level of service and expertise.\n\nAs an active member of the community, Tim has spoken at international, regional, and local venues including SQLBits, the SQL PASS summit, SQL Connections, SQL Saturday events, and various user groups and PASS virtual chapters.  He is an active volunteer and speaker at the North Texas SQL Server User Group in Dallas and is an volunteer for PASS.\n\nTim is coauthor of the book SQL Server Integration Services Design Patterns, and is a contributing author of the book MVP Deep Dives 2.

summary: I work with senior executives and entrepreneurs to transform their leadership performance and the organizational culture, while significantly impacting sales growth and profitability, and dramatically improving business performance.\n\nMy work is specialized in overcoming issues that impact business performance, for example between multi-cultural international operational units or between the head office, sales and operations.\n \nI regularly work with Chairmen, CEOs, Senior Executives and HR Directors who need and want to integrate capability, experience and skills from diverse cultures. \n \nThese conversations are frequently initiated by one or more of the following business drivers: \n \n•\tMulti-national companies needing to make deep changes to improve operational efficiency to reduce costs in mature markets\n•\tMulti-national businesses needing to be more customer focused and agile to combat competition from innovative start-ups\n•\tOrganic growth of a very large organization where succession planning, promotion and recruitment benefit from diversity\n•\tMergers and acquisitions where time to value from rapid multi-cultural team building is incredibly important\n•\tHigh Growth global businesses where senior team members and divisions need to perform and deliver extremely quickly.\n \nMy experience and credentials include:\n \n•\tAs an Executive Coach running a boutique international management consultancy since 1990 I have successfully completed client projects of various sizes and complexities, right up to multi-national level\n•\tAs an Adjunct Professor I taught in a Top 10 BBA program, I have a PhD in Business Administration, I’m the author or co-author of 7 books and a keynote conference speaker.\n \nMy passion is to inform and equip existing and rising executives with increased self and social awareness, getting away from the spreadsheet and into the human equation, to identify, develop and release the full potential of human capital within major organisations.

summary: Rich Friesen is the creator and developer of the innovative and exclusive “Mind Muscles™” training process. He works with financial professionals, independent traders and entrepreneurs who want to expand their mental game to make more consistent profits. With in depth experience as a broker, floor trader, financial software developer and entrepreneur, he brings concrete real world experience to his clients. He is now translating his experience into the Mind Muscles Academy, online training for independent and professional traders who want increase profits by expanding their mental game.\n .\nDuring the years dedicated to building Mind Muscles™, he was an independent consultant to the financial industry specializing in intellectual property development and management. He also founded and built ePIT Systems, a software company which produced internet exchange software solutions for the regulated and OTC market places. At ePIT he designed and received eight significant patents on electronic trading interfaces. ePIT's systems and patent technology were purchased by Hitachi.\n .\nPrior to ePIT Systems, Mr. Friesen founded, built and sold Trade Management LLC, one of the most consistently profitable options and equity trading firms on the floor of the PSE. As a member of the Pacific Exchange, he also served as Exchange Director. summary: Christian Höferle (alternative spelling: Hoeferle) is a cultural business consultant with extensive experience in working with multinational companies.\nGerman by birth, American by choice, and Bavarian at heart, Christian is a fan of building bridges and not enthusiastic about walls. With his team at The Culture Mastery, LLC he helps people close the gap between their home culture and the target culture they are working with. \nHe is also known as The Culture Guy and hosts a podcast of the same title. \n\nTCM helps multinational organizations and their employees to work better together across cultures. When companies work internationally and expand outside of their home markets, their employees need to be effective in collaborating with people from cultures which are foreign to them. They need to be able to sell and market to customers with unfamiliar consumption preferences. Beyond the language barriers global professionals are confronted with different behaviors and ways of doing business. Failing to communicate, manage, inspire, and lead across cultural differences is a huge risk for these companies, and the lack of cultural competence can be a bottom-line relevant issue.\nComing from a bilingual and bi-cultural background, Christian has been working on various levels of cultural consulting/coaching/training, translation & interpretation and relocation assistance. He has helped in relocating and training individuals, families, and teams from Germany, Europe, South America, Asia, and other regions to the United States; and familiarizing them with the many details of settling into another work environment, a different culture and a new community. He also trained hundreds of Americans who went on work assignments outside of the U.S.\n\nSpecialties:  \n• Developing Global Leaders\n• Coaching, Training, Consulting, Mentoring\n• Mastermind Facilitator\n• Workshops/Training Programs\n• Destination Services

summary: Dr. Musgrove has been in involved in the Environmental and Healthcare fields most of her life. She is currently a USA Board Certified Naturopath, Clinical Hypnotherapist, and an Environmental Specialist.  \n\nShe and her daughter often work together helping businesses deal with employer/employee problems - resolving many of the anger based, and emotionally charged upsets, which plague the workplace and the overall health of the employees.  They teach many of our veterans PTSD coping skills, and speak to small groups on a variety of topics.\n\nNow that she is semi-retired, Janis is spending more time writing and just enjoying her travels.  As a multi-genre author, Doc's work has been used in university literature classes as well as in children's religious education. summary: At the age of 23, just finishing my training in Sydney with Telecom when I was transferred to Newcastle and put in-charge of a specialist field. With staff all older than me, and my second-in-charge 15 years senior, I’d been thrown in the “deep end” with the task of building a strong efficient team. We became one of the highest performing groups Nationally.\n\nIn my early 30’s I joined Nobbys Surf Life Saving Club, and in my 2nd year, I was voted in as the Club Captain and Zone Supervisor for Nobbys and 2 other clubs. I was now the same age as many of the executive team, but they all had far more experience than me. I’d gone from being the youngest to the least experienced, yet still the one with all of the accountability. In 4 years we trebled the number of active patrol members.\n\nAnd that was just the beginning. I then became the single father and full time carer of 3 very young sons, while still a director of 2 companies. \n\nMy life has been a mission and a passion to understand people; what drives them and motivated them to behave the way they do. Learning not just from formal studies, but also through an enriched life of personal experience I became a world authority on what makes each of us tick; a reputation that’s had me flown around the world by some of the biggest international companies.\n\nI’ve been and continue to be privileged to help people from all walks of life. People from all types of business, schools around the world and in their private and social lives to build stronger relationships. \n\nHow successful have I been? A website full of testimonial, both written and video, still coming in more than 5 years after I worked with the person. It's not just knowledge that I share, but my experiences as well!  \n\nThe same skills I've applied in business, have been beneficial in my social and private. They are unique and have a universal application, which you can use as well. Choose a time at www.alanstevens.com.au/call and let's see how I can best assist you.

summary: Lisa Ludovici is a Certified Medical Support Hypnosis Practitioner specializing in medical hypnosis.  In addition to her private hypnosis practice in New York City, she is the first medical hypnotist hired by the US Government to work within the Veteran’s Administration in neurology at the VA NY Harbor Healthcare System in Manhattan. As a provider in the CARF Accredited Interdisciplinary Pain Rehabilitation Program she teaches Veterans, using the power of their mind through hypnosis, how to reduce and eliminate pain, and accelerate healing. \n\nThrough the International Board of Hypnotherapy (IBH), Lisa is certified as a Master, Medical, Childbirth, Natal/Inter-Life/Past-Life Regression Hypnotist.  She received her training at the Hypnotherapy Academy of America in New Mexico. Lisa graduated from Pennsylvania State University with a Bachelor of Arts in Communications and received her education as a Life Coach from the Institute of Professional Excellence in Coaching (IPEC).  She is also a Neuro-Linguistic Programming and Healing Imagery Practitioner. \n\nLisa learned first hand how hypnosis could transform a life.  Diagnosed with chronic migraines at the age of three, she experienced an average of 17 migraines a month.  Rarely did she experience three consecutive pain free days.  During her training at the Hypnotherapy Academy of America, while working with her own hypnotherapist, she completely healed herself of migraines.  After experiencing this life changing transformational healing through the power of therapeutic hypnosis, Lisa left the corporate world and has since dedicated her life to sharing the mental, emotional, and physical healing power of hypnosis with others.  To this day she lives 100% migraine free.\n\nShe is passionate about helping people tap into the incredible power that's within. Her mission is to leave this planet better than she found it by helping individuals and communities heal.

summary: Rajani has more than 17 years of industry experience in behavioral trainings, project management and people development. Prior to his entrepreneurial stint, he was a People Manager with SAP Labs India for eleven years contributing to the organization’s growth by developing talents.  Rajani was identified as a high potential manager within the organization for two consecutive years as a mark to his contribution towards people development. He is a well-known lean & agile management trainer with immense experience as a coach/mentor for various lines of business in different organizations.\n\nRajani’s passion for developing people, his instant ability to connect with the audience, his knowledge and creativity on delivering the topics are some of his unique capabilities. He brings experiential learnings from the industry to ensure personal effectiveness for the participants. During these years, Rajani has transformed himself as an international trainer conducting extensive workshops in India, USA & Middle East.\n\nRajani holds a people management certificate from Dale Carnegie, Situational Leadership\nCertificate from Ken Blanchard, NLP certification from NFNLP Institute, TTT from OMI and\nCorporate Ed Group (Boston, US), Train the Trainer Excellence certification from Indian\nSchool of Business (Hyderabad, India). Being a certified facilitator, Rajani has trained more\nthan 6,500 people on various soft skills topics. In addition, he is also a renowned author and\nhas authored two life changing books. Recently, Rajani represented India as a speaker @SME\nWorld Summit - Dubai speaking on “What lies below the Iceberg”\n\nRajani received a bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering from Bharathiyar University,\nIndia in 2000. He was awarded the best outgoing student for the year.

summary: Sharon L Muir knows from personal experience that thoughts and beliefs are directly reflected in our lives.  Improving your life is an inside job.  In order to improve your life the internal reality has to shift.  Sharon does not just talk about what she believes she lives it.  She has focused most of her life studying and practicing to find the best ways to transform her life from the inside out.  The source of the stories in this book is this journey of personal growth and her need to find solutions that are “outside the box”.  \nSharon was born in 1955; is a graduate of the Barbara Brennan School of Healing Science and an expert in the art and science of Communication, Neuro-Linguistic Programming and Personal growth.  She has been coaching and consulting clients to improve their lives since 1990.  Her life experiences have given her the extraordinary ability to help others gain the clarity they need to dissolve limiting beliefs, discover their inner brilliance and change from the inside out.\nSharon is a popular and entertaining speaker, author and trainer in the field of Personal Transformation and she can be reached via her website.\n www.SharonLMuir.com

summary: I’m a sex and relationship mentor and professional sensual masseur based in Central London.\n\nI’m fascinated by human sexuality. I think sex is an incredibly important part of life, but for many people, sex and sexuality are things that just happen. But when we don’t work at understanding and improving our sexual selves or our partners, a sense of unhappiness or lack of fulfilment can affect our broader sense of self.\n\nI’ve made it my calling to teach people how to achieve better physiological and emotional sexual fulfilment within relationships. By improving sexual skills and incorporating more intimacy and better communication into our relationships we not only make the whole experience more satisfying but also enhance our own sense of self. \n\nI give private treatments. I speak about and lead workshops on sex and sexuality. I offer personal and professional training to single and groups in psychosensual and sensual massage as a practical tool to increase confidence and enhance foreplay and intimate love making.\n\nSpecialties:\n\nFor Men - Understanding and helping men in the area of sexual fulfillment, skills and sexual relationships to include erectile dysfunction, premature ejaculation, loss of libido, changes in sexuality/ orientation and better love making skills, unleashing the primal man within.\n\nFor Women - Fear of intimacy, lack of orgasm, unsatisfactory sex life, 40 something and single again, improving sexual confidence and lovemaking skills, unleashing the primal woman within.\n\nFor Couples - Expanding the sexual relationship, sexual; performance and training with improved skills in foreplay and understanding better the psychology of sex. Overcoming relationship conflict. Teach my male partner how to be a more assertive lover. Teach my female partner to be a more expressive confident lover.\n\n\nTo read my story of how I came to do what I do please read the attached article \n\nThe Making of a Maverick: The Birth of a Sex Mentor - written by Chrissie Rowell

summary: \nAlison has brought together her extensive experience of therapy sessions with adults and children to produce a\nreally innovative and highly effective character who children and adults alike, can identify with and apply and project\nreal life situations to help them to deal with them as Ollie might.\n\nA set of easy to read books that empower children and adults to choose what they want to feel rather than allow\nthemselves to be controlled by their feelings.\nA website to allow easy engagement for the audience with ideas, products and resources is under development.\n\n\nWe have a growing team of therapists teaching the concepts behind Ollie in schools, to the Police Force, Nurses\nand we are now supported by NHS England and the NSPCC list the Ollie books as a resource.\nOllie describes the subconscious mind as a huge library where everything they have\never learned is stored. There is a librarian and he is in charge of putting learning in\nboxes, he decides which box dependent on how the child feels when that learning is\ntaking place. The beauty of the memory boxes is they all have dates. Ollie learns that he can revisit those boxes no\nmatter how daunting, now that he is an older version of himself with more capabilities and super power\nMore often\nthan not, we can then re-label that box in a much more positive and empowering way. This is having amazing an\neffect on children from abused back grounds\nOllie is aimed at children but the lessons in the books are\nfor young and old\n Adults are utilising the concepts for\nthemselves as well as with their children\nWe offer bespoke support packages to supply training on\nthe Ollie concept to those in organisations who would\nbenefit and also ‘one to one’ therapeutic intervention if\nrequired. We are not about reinventing the wheel we are\nall about helping you finding the right solution for every\nindividual\nPlease contact us on Info@ollieandhissuperpowers.com\n

summary: Are integrity and being in / acting from your heart important values for you? \nWelcome to my coaching! Face to face or on the phone.\nContact me and discover the person, who you really want to be(come).\n\nIn our coaching sessions we focus on achieving your goals. To this end, I will support you by initiating and eliciting change processes, and you will develop the urge and rediscover your nascent abilities to become who you truly are. Finally achieving and living your full potential, be it in the professional realm, in your personal life, or in sport, is often the result of the coaching process.\nAs a coach, I am trained to listen and observe. We meet for one-on-one sessions, face to face, or by phone. Occasionally, I may ask you a few seemingly odd questions, thus eliciting new and creative thoughts and ideas. I am convinced that you already have all the resources and skills you will need to live a fulfilling life. My job is to assist you in activating and integrating your abilities, so you can access them at the appropriate moment.\nI am based in Basel, Switzerland. The lines blur the more open she becomes and embraces her creations and experiences.\u201d', u'title': u'Words of the Heart (volume two in the Embracing Souls series)'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2012.5 ~ now', u'description': u'Downey, CA \u2013 Gratitude is the name of the day! We\u2019re celebrating people who have given so much to others at the 2nd Annual Touching Lives TV Award Show on Thursday, Dec. 5th, 7:30 pm at the Downey Civic Theatre\n \nEntertainers including Florence LaRue of the 5th Dimension, Broadway Star Raymond Patterson, \u201cThe Red Hat Mamma\u201d singer/songwriter/musical playwright/TV host Kathy Bee, Sebastian Sidi, Kulayd, Mario Raven & choir, Julie Simpson to name a few will bring unforgettable music to add to this celebration of admiration and appreciation. Talk Show Host Sheila O is on hand to welcome and interview celebrities and VIPs on the Red Carpet, while renowned photo-journalist Vinni Ratcliff will be snapping the pictures.\n\nThe TV Show Touching Lives was created during the time show producer Kathy Hampton AKA Kathy Bee was helping her dear friend Mary Stevenson (author of the famous poem \u201cFootprints In The Sand\u201d) gain recognition for her (author unknown) work.  Bee strongly believed that so many unsung heroes could be recognized though her positive, supportive TV Show of \u201cPeople Helping People\u201d. 10 years later, Bee produced hosted and aired 250 Touching Lives cable TV shows in Southern California.  \n\nWhen Kathy became the Chair of The Corporate Board of the Downey Regional Medical Center in 2008, the CEO of 35 years was let go. summary: Diligent, Professional, Award-Winning Golf Coach with Excellent Organizational Management Skills and Proven Public Relations Record. Detail-oriented professional who has a long standing record of over 10 years utilizing expertise, training and passion for golf to train, create special events, forge media partnerships, conceptualize and manage travel itineraries for multiple people. Stellar record successfully managing the fiscal budget of a BIG East Conference Division I Golf Program at Georgetown University. Adept at cultivating partnerships and increasing social media platforms and following base.\n\nI am currently writing my dissertation to complete with my Ph.D. in Athletic Administration/Sport Management with a minor in telecommunications from Indiana University, Bloomington (IUB). At IU, I was a doctoral student while serving as the Assistant Women's Golf Coach. My path through higher education began in South Bend, IN where I received my Bachelor of Arts in Sociology from the University of Notre Dame. I captained the Women’s Golf Team for two years. I obtained my Master’s of Science degree in Athletic Administration/Sport Management from IU. I have experience in the sport industry as a student-athlete, coach, PGA and Symetra Tour Caddie, and as an instructor at various sports camps (Stanford, Indiana, Notre Dame). I have enjoyed traveling to three continents and eleven foreign countries to either play golf competitively, teach or recruit. \n\nI have experience in compliance, fundraising, and event planning. I have worked in intercollegiate athletic departments for over a decade and am actively involved with NACWAA, LPGA, and Alliance of Women Coaches.\n\nSpecialties: sport management/athletic administration, telecommunications, recruiting, golf swing analysis, sport psychology, player development, fundraising, communications, management, marketing and PR, event planning, coaching, research, women's golf, women's sports and Title IX.

summary: Independent consultant, providing staff development in corporate or educational settings. I welcome the opportunity to serve your training needs.\n\nMy goal is to work closely with companies, schools, districts, educational service cooperatives and at the university level to evaluate, plan, design and deliver staff development that meets the changing needs of today's educators. \n\nI specialize in classroom management, in-class support for teachers (coaching), differentiated instruction and technology integration for student success. With nearly 20 years of experience as an educator, an educational consultant, and as a professional development provider, I can make a difference in your school.\n\nI am a certified national trainer for the Center for Teacher Effectiveness, presenting classroom management and differentiated instruction workshops to schools and school districts across the country. \n\nI also contract with Discovery Education, a Discovery Channel company, and recently co-wrote a national professional development course for that organization on academic achievement for English language learners.  \n\nIn addition, I served as the Online Professional Development Coordinator for the Arkansas Department of Education (ADE) before beginning my consulting and professional development training business. I have served as an adjunct professor, teaching graduate-level Education courses for several universities; as well as creating and teaching college-level Psychology and Spanish courses.\n\nI received my MS in Counseling Psychology from the University of Central Arkansas, my BA in the Humanities from Hendrix College, and a special certification in Spanish pedagogy from the University of Chile, in Santiago, Chile.\n

2003\n', u'title': u'Professional Leadership'}, {u'timePeriod': u'2014.10 ~ 2014.10', u'description': u'Poster presentation at the Global Health Symposium: Building on the Power of Partnerships at Henry Ford Health System\n\nAs a University of Michigan President\u2019s Advisory Committee on Labor Standards and Human Rights summer 2014 grant recipient, I spent three months in Phnom Penh, Cambodia completing a female garment workers\u2019 health issue analysis and proposing interventions that improve the occupational safety and health and personal health of individuals in the garment sector.\n\nIn Cambodia, over 400,000 people are employed by manufacturers to make clothing and shoes for major Western brands. Ninety percent of the workers are women, and the majority are under 25 years of age.  In recent years, mass psychogenic faintings in the factories have led NGOs to investigate the working and living conditions of the female garment workers in Cambodia.  Research has shown that 19% of garment workers are undernourished and anemic, and many more experience occupational stress, food- and water-borne diseases, elevated risk of unsafe abortions and sexually transmitted infections, exposure to hazardous materials and conditions, forms of harassment, forced overtime, and low wages. Completing a literature review on the limited data available, reviewing current practices, and conducting key informant interviews, I proposed interventions (e.g., electrolyte replenishment at a mid-shift break and nutritional counseling) to promote integrated health for workers inside the factories and at home that will be included in a memorandum of understanding to be presented to the brands to ensure workers\u2019 safety and health. I assess needs and provide for or design professional development experiences to further the quality of teaching and learning in schools.  \n\nI am a creative leader and innovative thinker.  Outside of work, I would hope you would find me having an adventure.  (Preferably someplace warm and on the water!) I am an artist and music lover.  My favorite musical artists would be the multi-talented Eric Long, whose voice is heavenly, and Jacob Long who plays the drums as if he has no choice.  (It is who he is, and he is amazing.) I am also the proud mom of Caleb Long who's great desire to impact the world and help others mirrors my own.

summary: AWARENESS: Do you know what’s right and true for you?\nACTION: Are you ready to make a real change?\nACCOUNTABILITY: Who’s on your team to help you make change happen?\n\uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11\nWorking together, we find answers to these questions and use them to develop solutions you can put into practice at work and in your personal life. My job is to challenge you to go outside your comfort zone and help you discover and act on what’s right and true for you. We’ll collaborate to create powerful, transformational processes that will move you toward true success . . . on your terms.\n\n\uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11\nCoaching for CHANGEMAKERS\nYou’re self-motivated, experienced, successful, and overwhelmed by a mighty challenge on your plate. Perhaps you’ve sought out this challenge, or maybe it’s been handed to you. Either way, you need someone to support you as you rise to the occasion. Changemakers are leaders. Everyone wants a piece of them. They work hard for their organizations, their causes, and their families. All this work leaves little time for reflection, creativity, and balance. \nSound like you? Contact me to set up a free, no-obligation sample coaching session.\n\n\uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11\nCoaching for LEARNERS\nBeing an aspiring coach can feel overwhelming. How do take your classroom training and take the leap into building your own practice? I’ve been there, and that’s why I’m passionate about helping aspiring coaches build their skills and their confidence. Tap my 20 years of experience and pick up pro tips you can use in your own practice.\n\n\uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11 \uD83C\uDF11\nPROFESSIONALS I HELP: women in leadership roles, entrepreneurs, executives, program managers, senior HR directors \nAREAS OF EXPERTISE:   professional development coaching, leadership development, personal coaching, training, public speaking, coaching supervision\nhttp://coacholk.com/individual-coaching/ \nhttp://coacholk.com/upcoming-events/ \n
